<section id="outline-container-orga230f47" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orga230f47">About me</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orga230f47">
<p>
I'm currently <a href="https://linguistics.mit.edu/user/pdell/">a visiting faculty member in the linguistics &amp; philosophy department at MIT</a>.
</p>

<p>
I'm a theoretical linguist, which means that my work involves developing formal models of what we know when we know a language. Mostly, I work on semantics and pragmatics; I'm also interested in computational approaches to meaning and the syntax-semantics interface.
</p>

<p>
When I'm not doing linguistics, I code, run, and scale vertical walls. Reach me at <a href="mailto:patrick.d.elliott@gmail.com">patrick.d.elliott@gmail.com</a>.
</p>
</div>
</section>

